## Java-Based Configuration in Spring

---

### 🧠 Why Java Config?

Spring started with **XML config** → then **Annotations** → then **Java-based config**.

```
Evolution:
XML Config (beans.xml)     →  verbose, hard to refactor
Annotation Config          →  @Component, @Autowired
Java Config ✅             →  pure Java, type-safe, no XML at all
```

| Config Style | File | Spring Boot? |
|---|---|---|
| XML | `beans.xml` | ❌ Old |
| Annotation | `@Component` scan | ✅ |
| Java Config | `@Configuration` class | ✅ Default |

> Spring Boot uses **Java-based config internally** — understanding this explains how Spring Boot auto-configuration works.

---

### 📌 Two Key Annotations

| Annotation | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `@Configuration` | This class = replacement for `beans.xml` |
| `@Bean` | This method = replacement for `<bean>` tag |

```xml
<!-- XML way -->
<bean id="student" class="com.example.Student"/>
```

```java
// Java Config way
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

    @Bean
    public Student student() {
        return new Student();
    }
}
```

