### 📌 @Bean — Details

```java
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

    // Default bean id = method name = "student"
    @Bean
    public Student student() {
        return new Student("Nivas", 21);
    }

    // Custom bean id
    @Bean(name = "myStudent")
    public Student anotherStudent() {
        return new Student("Balaji", 22);
    }

    // Multiple names
    @Bean(name = {"st", "studentBean", "myBean"})
    public Student yetAnother() {
        return new Student("Ravi", 23);
    }
}
```

