### 📌 Injecting Dependencies — 3 Ways in Java Config

#### Way 1 — Method Call (most common)
```java
@Bean
public Student student() {
    Student s = new Student();
    s.setAddress(address());   // Spring returns singleton bean
    return s;
}
```

#### Way 2 — Method Parameter (cleaner)
```java
@Bean
public Student student(Address address) {   // Spring auto-injects address bean
    Student s = new Student();
    s.setAddress(address);
    return s;
}
```

#### Way 3 — @Autowired in Config class
```java
@Configuration
public class AppConfig {

    @Autowired
    private Address address;   // Spring injects before student() runs

    @Bean
    public Address address() {
        return new Address("Sathyamangalam", "Tamil Nadu");
    }

    @Bean
    public Student student() {
        Student s = new Student();
        s.setAddress(address);
        return s;
    }
}
```

