### 📌 @ComponentScan — Auto-detect beans

Instead of manually writing `@Bean` for every class, tell Spring to **scan a package**:

```java
@Configuration
@ComponentScan(basePackages = "com.example")   // scans all @Component classes
public class AppConfig {
    // No @Bean methods needed
    // Spring finds @Component, @Service, @Repository, @Controller automatically
}
```

```java
// Student.java
@Component          // Spring detects this automatically
public class Student {

    @Autowired
    private Address address;
}
```

